An illegal cannabis farm containing hundreds of plants has been seized by the police.It was discovered on Saturday at a property on Falkland Street in Middlesbrough, where the electricity supply had been bypassed so it could be used to power the farm.Cleveland Police said the building contained about 400 plants which were worth approximately Â£400,000.No-one has so far been arrested in connection with the find.
